  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building the Resilience of Communities Affected by Climate Change and Environmental Degradation in Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intends to support the government in its efforts to improving access to sustainable livelihoods solutions among communities the most affected by climate change in Guinea.  The project aims to improve the understanding on migration, environment and climate change nexus in areas with a focus on gender aspects, increasing capacities and awareness on concretely strengthening the resilience of communities that are most vulnerable to climate change in Guinea, especially women, providing livelihood solutions to communities most affected by climate change to improve their resilience, especially women.</narrative>
  </description>
